   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX BEING CONFORMED TO THE IMAGE OF THE SON OF GOD TO BE DELIVERED FROM THE EXPRESSION OF THE NATURAL LIFE Scripture Reading: Rom 5:10; 8:29-30; 1:17b; 6:19b, 22b; 12:2; 8:19 God's original creation of man: That man may have His image to express His glory and beauty.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>That man may receive Him as life to live by Him.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The result of man's fall: Destroying the image that God created for man.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Losing the position of receiving God as life.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>Christ's redemption by His vicarious death and His salvation in life Rom 5:10: Redeeming fallen men so that they may be justified by God and reconciled to God Rom 8:30.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Then regenerating, sanctifying, renewing, transforming, and conforming them to the image of the Son of God Rom 1:17b; 6:19b, 22b; 12:2; 8:29: Making them sons of God Rom 8:19.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>That Christ may become the Firstborn among many brothers Rom 8:29.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>That God may gain a corporate expression which is the mingling of His firstborn Son with His many sons.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Enabling the believers to enjoy God's salvation in life and to be delivered from the expression of the natural life: Having no self-boasting.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Having no self-esteem.</S>
   </TEXT>
